    "title": "UBJSON Typed-Array Count Marker Amplification Denial of Service",
    "short_description": "An endpoint that decodes attacker-supplied UBJSON with no count or size guard can be driven into CPU or memory exhaustion because the typed-array count marker `[$<type>#<count>]` lets a tiny payload declare an arbitrarily large element count.",
